Perfect for locals & tourists! Description Kelly Greens Golf & Country Club is an exceptional 18-hole championship course located in the scenic community of Iona, Florida. Just minutes from Fort Myers and the Gulf Coast, this beautifully designed course offers a blend of challenging play and stunning natural surroundings. Opened in 1988 with an honorary first round played by the legendary Sam Snead, the course features meticulously maintained fairways, strategic water hazards, and undulating greens that offer excitement for players of all skill levels.

Golfers can warm up or refine their swing at the club's top-tier practice facilities, which include a driving range, chipping areas, and putting greens. The elegant clubhouse provides a welcoming retreat, offering full dining options, a pro shop stocked with the latest gear, and spaces for social gatherings or private events. Whether you're a local golfer or visiting the Iona area, Kelly Greens Golf & Country Club ensures an unforgettable golf experience in a picturesque Florida setting. Kelly Greens Golf & Country Club Kelly Greens is a private-gated community with its main entrance from Summerlin Road. Gates for use by residents are located at Kelly and John Morris roads that connect with McGregor Blvd. KG is a “bundled community”. When you purchase a residence (house or condo) you automatically become a member/owner of KG Country Club that includes golf, tennis, fitness center, restaurant, clubhouse facilities including Wi-Fi, Activities Center and community wide cable T.V. The quarterly assessment that every owner pays includes all of those amenities. The community is financially sound. If needed an appropriate line of credit is available. Numerous capital improvements have been accomplished during the last ten years. The Club has a mid six figure fund earmarked for emergencies and future improvements. KG is a completely developed community. Residences, country club facilities, and common grounds have been updated and professionally maintained reflecting the ambiance of a well - established neighborhood. Housing Total equals 939 residences comprised of single - family homes and various models of condos. Over 85 percent of residences overlook the golf course and KG’s numerous lakes. Major features include an eighteen hole championship golf course, tournament level tennis courts, a recently upgraded 200 seat full service restaurant, a state of the art lounge, recently renovated fitness center, pool, snack bar and Activities Center. KG’s enjoyable lifestyle features numerous activities, clubs and events available to all residents. The KG Golf Course and its lakes present natural beauty for the enjoyment of all. The entire community is attractively landscaped with various species of mature palms, oaks and other trees indigenous to the region. Augmented with perennials, annuals and other plantings, our community is a very attractive place to live and play. KG’s large population of water, wading and other species of birds is an interesting attraction. Osprey and Bald Eagles are regular visitors. Other species that adopt our lakes are Wood Storks, Great Blue Herons, Egrets, White Pelicans, Anhingas, Cormorants, the rare pink spoonbills and many more. And don’t overlook the “friendly” gators that frequently are observed sunning along the shores of our golf course.
